               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-354-person2877">
                  THOMAS 
                  JONES
               <interp inst="t18300916-354-person2877" type="surname" value="JONES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-354-person2877" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-354-person2877" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18300916-354-viclabel1826" type="occupation">coach-smith</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-354-victim2876 t18300916-354-viclabel1826"></join>. On the 10th of August I lost a coat, waistcoat, and trousers from my box- I had seen them safe on the 9th; the prisoner lodged and slept with me for three or four years - my box was broken open.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. I believe you have been on the most intimate terms? A. No - we had not occasionally lent each other money and clothes to pawn; he never pawned my clothes with my consent.</p>
               <p>Q. Did you not swear before the Magistrate that you lived like brothers - that he had often pawned your clothes, but brought them back very honestly, and you had no doubt he would this time? A. I do not recollect it - I will not swear I did not; I was so agitated, I hardly know what I said - if I said so, very likely it was so.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-354-person2878">
                  GEORGE 
                  KING
               <interp inst="t18300916-354-person2878" type="surname" value="KING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-354-person2878" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-354-person2878" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker. I received these clothes from the prisoner on the 10th of August - I knew him before; he has regularly pawned in his own name - he had pawned wearing-apparel and redeemed it, for years.</p>
